$$\text{Wiener}(y|\alpha, \tau, \beta, \delta) =
\frac{\alpha^3}{(y-\tau)^{3/2}} \exp \! \left(- \delta \alpha \beta -
\frac{\delta^2(y-\tau)}{2}\right) \sum_{k = - \infty}^{\infty} (2k +
\beta) \phi \! \left(\frac{2k \alpha + \beta}{\sqrt{y - \tau}}\right)$$
